    ICommunicationCluster: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    The CommunicationCluster is the main element to describe the topological connection of communicating ECUs. A cluster describes the ensemble of ECUs, which are linked by a communication medium of arbitrary topology (bus, star, ring, ...). The nodes within the cluster share the same communication protocol, which may be event-triggered, time-triggered or a combination of both. A CommunicationCluster aggregates one or more physical channels. All physical channels that are aggregated by a communication cluster are synchronized with each other.
